## Formal Critical Reflection

This three-part formal critical reflection asks students to write a 5-7 page essay in which they a.) reflect back on their learning about data feminism and rhetorical data studies and forward their definitions of data; recall and identify best practices for doing data advocacy; b.) apply learning to describe and analyze a data advocacy website.
